Task 28-25-00-810-802-A

Refuel-Valve System Failure in Auto Control (Fails to Open) - (20150201)

Effective on: 001-999
WARNING:   
OBEY THE FUEL SAFETY PROCEDURES.
WARNING:   
WHEN YOU DO WORK ON THE FUEL SYSTEM WIRING, YOU MUST USE TEST EQUIPMENT THAT IS APPROVED (REFER TO INTERNATIONAL OR NATIONAL SPECIFICATIONS FOR INTRINSICALLY SAFE TEST EQUIPMENT: EN50020, UL913 OR EQUIVALENT). TEST EQUIPMENT THAT IS NOT APPROVED CAN CAUSE FIRE OR AN EXPLOSION.
CAUTION:   
DO NOT LET THE REFUEL PRESSURE BE MORE THAN THE MAXIMUM SAFE PRESSURE OF 50psi (3.45bar).

    3. Fault Confirmation

    Effective on: 001-999

    SUBTASK 28-25-00-710-052 -A0 - (20130201)

    A. Make sure that the steps in the pressure refuel with auto control SEE AMM 12-11-28-650-003 , are complied with.
    NOTE:   
    The refuel valve will not open if the related tank is full of fuel.

    4. Fault Isolation

    Effective on: 001-100

    SUBTASK 28-25-00-810-052 -A0 - (20130201)

    A. Procedure
    (1) If the fault continues:
    •

    do the pressure refuel with manual control SEE AMM 12-11-28-650-004 .

    (2) If the fault continues with manual control:
    •

    do
    Effective on: 001-100 28-25-00-810-803-A .

    (3) If the refuel system operates correctly with manual control:
    •

    set the MCDU to:

    (a) The SYSTEM REPORT/TEST (FUEL).
    (b) The FQIS STATUS page.
    (4) Replace any LRUs listed on the FQIS STATUS page. Do the applicable troubleshooting procedure.
    (5) Do the pressure refuel with auto control.
    (6) If the fault continues:
    (a) Set the MCDU to INPUT PARAMETERS page 3, (the bit position - state cross-reference).
    (b) Examine the bit positions in the Table that follows:

    NOTE:   
    The preselector(s) INC/DEC switch input to the FQIC will only show a 1 while the INC/DEC switch is held in that position. Not at the central/rest position.
    (7) For the automatic refuel mode to be active check the conditions that follow in conjunction with the Table above:
    (a) The ground/flight discrete input is set to ground.
    (b) The refuel selected discrete is active. The logic for this, incorporated in the aircraft wiring, is condition 1_ or 2_ below:
    1 Refuel panel door open and the MODE SELECT switch on the external refuel panel set to REFUEL.
    (c) All the REFUEL VALVE switches are set to NORMAL.
    (8) For an automatic refuel to start make that the conditions are as follows:
    (a) Refuel bus power has been present for more than 7 seconds.
    (b) Automatic refuel mode is active (see Para. 7).
    (c) The displayed preselector FQ is 100kg (200lb) greater than the actual fuel quantity.

    (11) If the fault continues replace the FQIC (3QT)   SEE AMM 28-42-34-000-001 and SEE AMM 28-42-34-400-001 >.
